Rounded Mplus 1c Thin Regular (RoundedMplus1c-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Rounded Mplus 1c' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Rounded Mplus 1c Thin'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Rounded Mplus 1c' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Rounded Mplus 1c Light'.

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'RoundedMplus1c-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'RoundedMplus1c-Medium', Everything looks good.

Rounded Mplus 1c Medium Regular (RoundedMplus1c-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Rounded Mplus 1c' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Rounded Mplus 1c Medium'.

Rounded Mplus 1c ExtraBold Regular (RoundedMplus1c-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Rounded Mplus 1c' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Rounded Mplus 1c ExtraBold'.

Rounded Mplus 1c Black Regular (RoundedMplus1c-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Rounded Mplus 1c' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Rounded Mplus 1c Black'.
